snippet: Rescuers recovered the bodies of 11 more climbers from Mount Kinabalu, Malaysia’s highest peak, on Saturday, a day after it was struck by a magnitude 5.9 earthquake.
abstract: Rescuers recover bodies of 11 more climbers from Mount Kinabalu, Malaysia’s highest peak, after it was struck by a magnitude 5.9 earthquake; 13 deaths have been attributed to quake.
lead_paragraph: Rescuers recovered the bodies of 11 more climbers from Mount Kinabalu, Malaysia’s highest peak, on Saturday, a day after it was struck by a magnitude 5.9 earthquake.

headline.main: 13 Climbers Dead After Earthquake Strikes Malaysian Peak
headline.print_headline: 13 Climbers Dead After Earthquake Strikes Malaysian Peak
